{
  "stem": "15082.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think my dad was the one that guided us, and watched over us, and knew how to-- every time, when there was some problems, how to deal with it to keep us together.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] The first time that they came in, and they grabbed a bunch of people to be sent to Sasow, the camp, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was grabbed as a young boy in the street.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as the transport was leaving, my dad exchanged himself for me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He went to Sasow.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I remained with my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that's the time that we were separated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] the Polish man that was a very close friend of my dad's, Mr.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[POLISH], came up and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] said to us, if we ever needed, we could come to his house and stay with him.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In the meantime, he used to go about once a month to Sasow, which I would say was 25 kilometers or so, and bring some packages of food to my dad to camp there.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That's how close he was to my dad.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The year that my father was taken to Sasow was in the year of 1942, Sasow in the year of 1942, in the fall.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "16.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father stayed in that camp [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] up to the-- sometimes in the-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] summer of the following year, which would bring us up to 1943.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In between, I was taken to Sasow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from Sasow, they had sent me to Lackie, which was about 20 kilometers away or so.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By-- grabbed again.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Podkamien, we still stayed in our house.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And every once in awhile, they'd have to give a quote of people.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
